South Korean international Lee Keun-Ho is named as Asian Footballer of the Year in a ceremony held in Kuala Lumpur. Shinji Kagawa, Japanese midfielder of Manchester United, is the first recipient of the Asian International Footballer of the Year award. (AFC) (Goal.com)In volleyball, Russia's Lokomotiv Novosibirsk defeats Italy's Bre Banca Lannutti Cuneo 3–2 in the thriller final to win the 2012–13 CEV Champions League. (CEV)Italy's Juventus and France's Paris Saint-Germain reach 2012–13 UEFA Champions League quarter-finals defeating Celtic and Valencia respectively. (CNN) (CBC) (Reuters)